# <type>: <subject> (max 50 chars)
#
# <body> - Explain what and why (max 72 chars per line)
#
# Types:
# feat: new feature
# fix: bug fix
# docs: documentation changes
# style: formatting, missing semicolons, etc
# refactor: code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# perf: performance improvement
# test: adding missing tests
# chore: maintain, dependencies, build tools
# security: security fixes or improvements
# breaking: breaking changes (use ! after type)
#
# Example:
# feat: add email notification scheduling
#
# - Implement cron-based scheduler for email notifications
# - Add user preference settings for notification timing
# - Include HTML email templates with meeting summaries
# - Add database logging for sent notifications
#
# Closes #123